  "texts": [
    "van Benthem 2010, § 9.4).Example 6.18 (Correspondence by Minimal Valuations).",
    "Given a frame F, what is the minimal way of making the antecedent of □ i q → □ i □ i q true at a state x?",
    "If F were a full world frame, the minimal way of making □ i q true at x would be with a valuation π such that π(q) = R i (x).",
    "However, if F is a standard full possibility frame, the minimal admissible way of making □ i p true at x is with a valuation π such thatπ(q) = int(cl(R i (x))) = {z ∈ S | ∀w ⊑ z ∃w ′ ⊑ w: xR i w ′ }.",
    "(6.1) Since R i (x) is a downset by R-down, this π(q) is the minimal regular open set including R i (x) by Fact 2.17.2."
  ],
